From 6ea034aba47d16b5bb62655b48e90058f0469378 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: DAWN Sandbox <dawn-agent@regent.local>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 11:16:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add multi-file upload to Library, remove duplicate upload tab
 from Memory
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Wired the existing but unused POST /ingest/files backend endpoint to
  the Books/Library upload panel. The file input now accepts multiple
  files; selecting more than one switches to the batch path
  (ingestFiles), queuing one job per file and tracking each in the
  existing upload-jobs list/poller. Single-file selection still uses
  the original ingestFile call so custom titles keep working.
- Added ingestFiles() + IngestFilesResponse to lib/api.ts.
- Removed the Memory page's 'Upload File' tab entirely. It duplicated
  Books' upload but only fired ingestFile() directly with no book
  record created afterward, so uploads through it were untracked and
  invisible in the Library. Memory now focuses on pending-node review,
  repo/document ingestion, and the ingestion log — Library is the
  single place to upload and track book-like content.
